name: Modular 'Shapes of London' glowing sculpture
description:
The Shard, The Gherkin, BT Tower, London Eye, Battersea Power Station, Tower Bridge, Big Ben, Nelson’s Column and The New Bus for London. Accurate to scale.

The blue, orange, red, green, yellow and clear perspex pieces can be moved around (between and along the slots) to create different compositions and colour combinations.
When placed on a tablet the pieces glow through the edges and through the etchings on both faces.
Shown on an ipad. Tallest piece (The Shard) is 20cm.

Limited edition. Signed by the artist.
Made per order so can take up to 2 weeks before posting.

Shipping: 
Inside the UK: £5. With other item: £5
Anywhere else in the world: £12.50. With another item: £12.50

name: Shapes of London/NYC/SF. A2 limited edition screenprint.
description: London: The Shard, The Gherkin, BT Tower, London Eye, Battersea Power Station, Tower Bridge, Big Ben, Nelson's Column and The New Bus for London. Accurate to scale. NYC: Empire State Building, Statue of Liberty, Washington Sq. arch, Guggenheim Museum, Bank of America Tower, One WTC, Three WTC, Conde Nast Building, NY Life Building. Accurate to scale. San Francisco: Ferry Building, Golden Gate Bridge, Palace of Fine Arts, City Hall, Transamerica Pyramid, Russ building, Cable car, Coit tower. Accurate to scale. Silkscreen screenprinted in London by Dan Mather. A2 (594x420 mm / 23.4x16.5 in) limited edition of 50, signed & numbered. Water-based Pantone colour match inks, each colour overprinted resulting in more than just the 8 spot colours. Printed on 260gsm Fedrigoni Freelife Vellum Cream stock. Archival and 100% acid-free so no discolouration in years to come. Carefully rolled in acid free tissue paper in thick, protective cardboard tubes and posted Recorded Delivery. Free shipping to anywhere in the world. Detailed images Also available as a Giclée print
